snippet.textDisplay:
Whitlock is hard to root for in most segments but despite his constant reiteration, he is right.
The problem is Jerry Jones & his family wont let his coaches coach.

Mike McCarthy is known for having archaic playbooks & keeping his cool. McCarthy also doesnt have a strength in football. What is Mike known for? Defense? Special teams? Offense? Mike is known for nothing because that is his football specialty. Mike McCarthy is quiet, level headed, and amicable.

So if the Jones' family hands are too close to the Koolaid and messing the team's success up, then Mike was hired because is likeable so Jerry can be around him. Why? Because Jerry will be around the team and the media. Mike will only be there to take heat from losses. Jerry know mike will shut and try to appease everyone. Basically the problem is Jerry and jerry just got a coach that will only be a slightly better version of Jason Garrett. So the Cowboys will make the playoffs & lose every 1st game like the bengals used too.
